data.title: From Gothic to good eats in picturesque Fribourg (& there will be cheese!)
data.meta_description: The medieval town of Fribourg, founded in 1157, is a treasure trove of Gothic architecture and a regional epicentre for the art of good eating, finds Sandy Guy
data.text:
Surrounded on three sides by the Sarine River, Fribourg is one of the largest medieval towns in Switzerland, with more than 200 unique Gothic facades dating from the 15th century.

The river skirts the edge of Basse-Ville — lower town — dividing the city into two sectors: German-speaking and French-speaking.
